{
  "texts": [
    "We observe that DeGCG outperforms GCG-M and GCG-M w/ domain data in terms of ASR performance across five of the six categories.",
    "The inclusion of domain data significantly enhances performance, particularly in the Chemical biological, Misinformation, Illegal, and Cybercrime categories.",
    "The relatively lower ASR performance in the Harmful and Harassment Bully categories could be attributed to the limited data size in these categories.",
    "Nonetheless, the success of the behavior-agnostic suffix transferring underscores the efficacy of FTS, validating the necessity of the decoupled first-token searching and content-aware search process.",
    "Interleaved Self-Transferring."
  ]
}